==English==

===Etymology===
From Hindustani [[गुरू]] / {{URchar|[[گرو]]}} < Sanskrit [[गुरु]], meaning [[heavy]]. An etymology based on the Advayataraka [[Upanishad]] (14--18, verse 5) describes the syllables '''gu'''=darkness and '''ru'''=dispeller, as in '''dispeller of darkness'''.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
#A [[Hindu]] spiritual teacher.
#An [[advisor]] or [[mentor]].
#:''He acted as her '''guru''', giving much needed advice over the years.''
#A leader or [[expert]] in a field.
#:''The Wiktionary '''guru''' made many helpful contributions.''

